# Brand Intelligence (Project Override)

**IMPORTANT:** This project stores brand data as flat files in the repo, NOT in a SQLite database. Do NOT call `list_brand_sections`, `read_brand_section`, `list_brand_assets`, or `run_brand_check` MCP tools — they do not apply here.

## Where Brand Data Lives

All brand rules are documented in `BRAND.md` (the primary reference). Read it first for any styling, layout, or content work.

For deeper brand knowledge, read from `brand/`:

| Need | Read |
|------|------|
| Color rules | `brand/patterns/color-palette.md` |
| Font rules | `brand/patterns/typography.md` |
| Brushstroke rules | `brand/patterns/brushstroke-textures.md` |
| Circle/underline emphasis | `brand/patterns/circles-underlines.md` |
| Footer structure | `brand/patterns/footer-structure.md` |
| Decorative minimums | `brand/patterns/decorative-minimums.md` |
| FLFont tagline patterns | `brand/patterns/flfont-tagline-patterns.md` |
| Layout archetypes | `brand/patterns/layout-archetypes.md` |
| Opacity system | `brand/patterns/opacity-patterns.md` |
| Photo/mockup rules | `brand/patterns/photos-mockups.md` |
| Typographic treatments | `brand/patterns/typographic-treatments.md` |
| **All hard rules (weight 81+)** | `brand/hard-rules.md` |
| Voice & style guide | `brand/voice-guide/voice-and-style.md` |
| Product copy (per product) | `brand/voice-guide/products/*.md` |

## Weight System

Brand rules carry weights 1-100:
- **81-100** = must follow (brand-critical, blocking)
- **51-80** = should follow (strong preference)
- **21-50** = recommended (flexible)
- **1-20** = nice-to-have

## Layout Archetypes

Social post and one-pager layout skeletons are in `archetypes/social/`. Each archetype has `index.html` (skeleton), `schema.json` (slot definitions), and `README.md` (usage guide).

## Validation Tools

- `node tools/brand-compliance.cjs <file> --context web|social` — check brand rule compliance
- `node tools/dimension-check.cjs <file> --target instagram|linkedin_landscape|letter|slides` — check output dimensions

## Quick Reference

Read `BRAND.md` for the complete summary of fonts, colors, components, and rules. It is the single source of truth.
